@startuml vt2_availability

title VT2 — VehicleTime: Initialization and Readiness Check

skinparam backgroundColor white
hide footbox
autonumber "<font color=navy><b>[00]"

legend top left
    |= Color               |= Description                  |
    |<#LightSalmon>        | Application business logic    |
    |<#LightGreen>         | score::time framework         |
    |<#LightCoral>         | VehicleTime backend           |
endlegend

box "Application" #e6f0ff
    participant "Business\nlogic" as app #LightSalmon
end box

box "score::time" #f0fff0
    participant "VehicleClock" as clock #LightGreen
    participant "VehicleClockBackend" as backend #LightCoral
end box

app -> clock : GetInstance()
activate clock
clock --> app : handle
deactivate clock

== Step 1 — Init: open the IPC channel ==

app -> clock : Init()
activate clock
clock -> backend : Init()
activate backend
backend --> clock : true  (IPC channel open)
deactivate backend
clock --> app : true
deactivate clock

note right of clock
    is_ready_ = true.
    IsAvailable() now returns true.
    Now() returns real data.
end note

== Step 2 — Optional: non-blocking readiness probe ==

app -> clock : IsAvailable()
activate clock
clock -> backend : IsAvailable()
activate backend
backend --> clock : true
deactivate backend
clock --> app : true
deactivate clock

== Alternative: blocking wait with stop_token + deadline ==

app -> clock : WaitUntilAvailable(stop_token,\n  steady_clock::now() + 30s)
activate clock
loop until available OR deadline OR stop requested
    clock -> backend : IsAvailable()
    activate backend
    backend --> clock : bool
    deactivate backend
end
clock --> app : true (became available)
deactivate clock

note left of app
    Only Clock<Tag> domains that require
    explicit initialization expose Init(),
    IsAvailable() and WaitUntilAvailable().
    HighResSteadyTime / SteadyClock / SystemClock
    are always ready — calling these methods
    on them is a compile error.
end note

@enduml
